    {
      "instruction": "<p>Add the <strong>smoky chicken stacks</strong> to a baking tray lined with<strong> tin foil </strong>(to avoid mess!)</p><p>Add a drizzle of <strong>olive oil</strong> and a pinch of <strong>salt</strong> and <strong>pepper</strong> and put the tray in the oven for 20 min or until the chicken is cooked through (no pink meat!)</p><p>Meanwhile, peel and finely chop (or grate) the <strong>garlic</strong></p><p>Trim, then chop the <strong>spring onion<span class=\"text-danger\">[s]</span></strong></p><p>Drain the <strong>sweetcorn</strong></p>",
