    {
      "instruction": "<p>Heat a large, wide-based pan (preferably non-stick) with a drizzle of <strong>olive oil </strong>and a pinch of<strong> salt </strong>over a medium-high heat</p><p>Once hot, add the<strong> chopped garlic </strong>and <strong>spring onion </strong>and cook for 1-2 min or until softened</p><p>Add the<strong> drained sweetcorn</strong>,<strong> dried chilli flakes</strong> (can't handle the heat? Go easy!) and <strong>half</strong> the <strong>cider vinegar</strong> and cook for a further 1-2 min or until the vinegar has been absorbed</p>",
